<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Yesterday we did OPVL together. Today you do it on your own.</p>
  <p>The hardest OPVL move is naming a <strong>specific Limitation</strong> — not "this source might be biased" but "this source is funded by the company whose product it studies, which means its data on side effects is unlikely to be complete." That specificity is what the rubric's T/T strand is built to detect. Today is where you start building it.</p>
  <p>There's also a sub-move today: telling the difference between an <strong>observation</strong>, an <strong>inference</strong>, a <strong>claim</strong>, and an <strong>opinion</strong>. Every source mixes these. OPVL on Value and Limitations gets sharper when you can label which is which.</p>
</section>

